new_version_errors.0.5.0:
The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '0.5.0' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name_under[0] }}/{{ name_under }}/{{ name_under }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "vegafusion-python-embed" %}
{% set name_under = "vegafusion_python_embed" %}
{% set version = "0.10.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name_under[0] }}/{{ name_under }}/{{ name_under }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 059cfb7d57d9bd49de0ceeaae98c1f65c10f77bb6967057b4a2808b599ae16c8

build:
  number: 1
  script: |
    cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output THIRDPARTY.yml
    {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}  # [win]
    - {{ compiler('rust') }}
    - protobuf
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - maturin
  run:
    - python

test:
  requires:
    - pip
  commands:
    - pip check

about:
  home: https://vegafusion.io
  license: AGPL-3.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file:
    - LICENSE
    - THIRDPARTY.yml

  summary: Server-side acceleration for the Vega visualization grammar
  description: |
    VegaFusion provides serverside acceleration for the Vega visualization grammer. The vegafusion-python-embed
    package is generally used as a dependency of higher-level, pure-Python, packages like vegafusion-jupyter.
  doc_url: https://vegafusion.io
  dev_url: https://github.com/vegafusion/vegafusion

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dhirschfeld
    - jonmmease
